title: Study: Elevation of Salon Wall, Prince of Hesse Palace
provenance: Collection Destailleur, catalog number 152, Collection of Leon Decloux.
medium: Pen and black ink, watercolor, gold paint
description: Sofa stands under an empty oblong frame and two pilaster strips and is flanked by wainscotted dados before the center of the wall.  A decorative panel with a fountain is at left.  Another with Ceres in clouds, at right.  Ink lines along edges.
name: Drawing
